ion is also given to the use of music and physical aspects of staging.Originally published in 1976.The Princeton Legacy Library uses the latest print-on-demand technology to again make available previously out-of-print books from the distinguished backlist of Princeton University Press. These editions preserve the original texts of these important books while presenting them in durable paperback and hardcover editions. The goal of the Princeton Legacy Library is to vastly increase access to the rich scholarly heritage found in the thousands of books published by Princeton University Press since its founding in 1905.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChinese dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aChinese dramaxYuan dynasty, 1260-1368xHistory and criticism. 0aChinese dramayYuan dynasty, 1260-1368xHistory and criticism. 0aChinese dramazYuan dynasty, 1260-1368xHistory and criticism. 0aChinese drama. 0aTheaterzChinaxHistory. 0aTheaterzChina. 0aTheater. 0aYuan Dynasty (China). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979z978311042684708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Literaturez978311041353308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140087109440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400871094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400871094.jpg  a978-3-11-041353-3  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package Literature  a978-3-11-042684-7  Princeton Legacy Lib. eBook Package 1931-1979c1931d1979  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton 